==English==
===Adjective===
'''hexadecimal'''

#(''mathematics, computing'') Hexadecimal (often abbreviated hex) is a base 16 numeral system, usually written using the symbols 0-9 and A-F. It is a particularly useful system with computers because there is an one to one mapping from four bits to the 16 hex digits.

